# Add Electronic Invoice Fields to Order Model

## Goal Description
The goal is to support ECPay Electronic Invoice integration by storing necessary invoice parameters in the [Order](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#214-363) model. This allows the application to capture user preferences (Carrier Type, Donation, etc.) during order creation and pass them to ECPay.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This change involves modifying the database schema. While SQLAlchemy models will be updated, **you (the user) are responsible for running the actual database migration SQL** (provided in [plans/šÂášĽîŠŞČŔęŽ.md](file:///c:/coding/template/plans/%E7%B6%A0%E7%95%8C%E6%B8%AC%E8%A9%A6.md)) to apply these changes to your database. This plan only updates the Python code to match the new schema.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend

#### [MODIFY] [order.py](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py)
- Update [Order](file:///c:/coding/template/backend/app/models/order.py#214-363) class to include the following new fields (Scheme V2):
    - `invoice_type` (String, default='2')
    - `carrier_type` (String)
    - `carrier_num` (String)
    - `donation` (String, default='0')
    - `love_code` (String)
    - `print_mark` (String, default='0')
    - `customer_identifier` (String)
    - `customer_name` (String, Optional)
    - `customer_addr` (String, Optional)
    - `customer_phone` (String, Optional)
    - `customer_email` (String, Optional)

